                <note rend="inline" type="source">693.002/705: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Consul General at Shanghai</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Lockhart</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1938-06-30T18:00:00-04:00"
                            >June 30, 1938—6 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>418. Your 899, June 24, 5 p.m., in regard to Chinese customs. Please ascertain,
                    if practicable, the list of “items favorable to the <pb facs="0739" n="735"
                        xml:id="pg_735"/> Japanese” that must “be implemented in full” before
                    contributions will be made by Japanese-controlled areas toward loan payments,
                    and inform the Department and Tokyo.</p>
                <p>Please repeat to Tokyo.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
